HEADWORD: Mesogastric
<hw>Mes`o*gas"tric</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Meso-</ets> + <ets>gastric</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Of or pertaining to
the middle region of the abdomen, or of the stomach.</def> <sd>(b)</sd>
<def>Of or pertaining to the mesogaster.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Of or pertaining to the middle
gastric lobe of the carapace of a crab.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Mesogastrium</ent>⟦br⟧
